{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3548078,"name":"","username":"KatilKedi","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/f14d63/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T10:05:29.939Z","cooked":"<p>We are at a competition right now and facing problems with Swerve controls. We tested it in Pratice Field and it was fine. However in match swerve controls inverted. Has anyone had a problem like this? Also I heard that the rotation of the robot can be reset during the match. If that is possible how can I apply it ti my code so that I can reset it whenever I want.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T10:05:29.939Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":64,"reads":254,"readers_count":253,"score":385.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":494329,"topic_slug":"swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":72140,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches/494329/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3548080,"name":"Aditya Gajula","username":"Aditya9246","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/fbc32d/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T10:19:08.650Z","cooked":"<p>A quick fix could be assigning a reset gyro command to button that resets gyro</p>
<p>in your drive subsystem:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public Command resetGyroCommand(){
    return this.runOnce(() -&gt; {
          this.resetGyroFunction();
    });
}
</code></pre>
<p>assign this command to a button like other commands.</p>
<p>Now, you should be able to reset the gyro everytime you want to reset robot heading in matches<br>
<a class="mention" href="/u/katilkedi">@KatilKedi</a></p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T10:19:08.650Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":250,"readers_count":249,"score":75.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":494329,"topic_slug":"swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches","display_username":"Aditya Gajula","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63857,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"1294 Programming Lead"},"post_url":"/t/swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches/494329/3","custom_user_title":"1294 Programming Lead","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548082,"name":"","username":"KatilKedi","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/f14d63/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T10:36:32.808Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks for your answer i will try it now. Also do you think resetting gyro will help us to solve our inverted controllers too?</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T10:36:32.808Z","reply_count":3,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":214,"readers_count":213,"score":57.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":494329,"topic_slug":"swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":63857,"username":"Aditya9246","name":"Aditya Gajula","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/fbc32d/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":72140,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches/494329/4","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548083,"name":"Aditya Gajula","username":"Aditya9246","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/fbc32d/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T10:46:50.327Z","cooked":"<p>When you say inverted controllers, I assume what’s happening is that on one alliance (let’s say blue), your controls are fine and on the other alliance (red), your controls are inverted.</p>
<p>If that’s your issue, then in matches that you are on the inverted alliance, make sure your robot’s front side faces away from the driver station (like the robot’s rear/back side faces your driveteam) and then press the reset gyro button (make sure robot is straight, maybe align the robot by driving against the reef or a wall).</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T10:46:50.327Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":209,"readers_count":208,"score":51.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":494329,"topic_slug":"swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches","display_username":"Aditya Gajula","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":72140,"username":"KatilKedi","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/f14d63/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63857,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"1294 Programming Lead"},"post_url":"/t/swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches/494329/5","custom_user_title":"1294 Programming Lead","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548084,"name":"","username":"Hollisms","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T10:47:10.684Z","cooked":"<p>Depends on your code…</p>
<p>Most likely you need to multiply your joystick input by -1 depending on what alliance you are on.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T10:47:52.626Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":195,"readers_count":194,"score":74.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":494329,"topic_slug":"swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":72140,"username":"KatilKedi","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/f14d63/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36169,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Software Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches/494329/6","custom_user_title":"Software Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1},{"id":"point_up","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548086,"name":"Aditya Gajula","username":"Aditya9246","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/fbc32d/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T10:48:46.459Z","cooked":"<p>if you are able to link your code that we can refer to, we can specify where you might have to invert your inputs if needed.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T10:48:46.459Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":181,"readers_count":180,"score":51.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":494329,"topic_slug":"swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches","display_username":"Aditya Gajula","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":72140,"username":"KatilKedi","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/f14d63/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63857,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"1294 Programming Lead"},"post_url":"/t/swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches/494329/7","custom_user_title":"1294 Programming Lead","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548088,"name":"","username":"KatilKedi","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/f14d63/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T10:55:55.771Z","cooked":"<p>That looks like our problem but i dont think i understand the solution. Can you please explain a little bit more?</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T10:55:55.771Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":174,"readers_count":173,"score":39.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":494329,"topic_slug":"swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":63857,"username":"Aditya9246","name":"Aditya Gajula","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/fbc32d/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":72140,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches/494329/8","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548089,"name":"","username":"KatilKedi","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/f14d63/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T10:58:11.174Z","cooked":"<p>We have a code like<br>
'joystick0.leftBumper().onTrue(drivetrain.runOnce(() → drivetrain.seedFieldCentric()));<br>
But it doesnt seem to work. Also our code is generated with Phoenix Tuner.</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T10:58:11.174Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":166,"readers_count":165,"score":48.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":494329,"topic_slug":"swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":63857,"username":"Aditya9246","name":"Aditya Gajula","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/fbc32d/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":72140,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches/494329/9","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548090,"name":"","username":"Hollisms","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T11:04:48.064Z","cooked":"<p>For <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> swerve template.</p>
<p><a class="mention" href="/u/bhall-ctre">@bhall-ctre</a> if you haven’t already you may want to update the template…</p>
<p>Note operator perspective</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">private void configureBindings() {
        // Note that X is defined as forward according to WPILib convention,
        // and Y is defined as to the left according to WPILib convention.
        drivetrain.setDefaultCommand(
                // Drivetrain will execute this command periodically
                drivetrain.applyRequest(() -&gt; drive
                        .withForwardPerspective(ForwardPerspectiveValue.OperatorPerspective)
                        .withVelocityX(-getDriverYVelocity()) // Drive forward with negative Y(forward)
                        .withVelocityY(-getDriverXVelocity()) // Drive left with negative X (left)
                        .withRotationalRate(-getDriverRotationalRate()) // Drive
                                                                        // counterclockwise
                                                                        // with
                // negative X (left)
                ));
</code></pre>","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T11:49:35.427Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":166,"readers_count":165,"score":43.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":494329,"topic_slug":"swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":72140,"username":"KatilKedi","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/f14d63/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36169,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Software Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches/494329/10","custom_user_title":"Software Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548092,"name":"Aditya Gajula","username":"Aditya9246","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/fbc32d/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T11:18:36.172Z","cooked":"<p>If you’re using field-centric control (where movement is relative to the field, not the robot), make sure your gyro is correctly zeroed at the start of the match.</p>
<ul>
<li>On <strong>Red Alliance</strong>, facing the <strong>Red Driver Station</strong>, both <strong>robot-oriented and field-oriented headings are 0°</strong>.</li>
<li>On <strong>Blue Alliance</strong>, facing the <strong>Blue Driver Station</strong>, the <strong>robot-oriented heading is 0°</strong>, but the <strong>field-oriented heading is 180°</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>To ensure consistent controls, reset the gyro when your robot is facing away from the driver station.</strong></p>
<p>There may be a simpler fix for <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> Phoenix Tuner swerve code, but I haven’t worked with it, so hopefully, someone can share a better solution.</p>","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T11:18:36.172Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":151,"readers_count":150,"score":70.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":494329,"topic_slug":"swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches","display_username":"Aditya Gajula","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":72140,"username":"KatilKedi","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/f14d63/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63857,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"1294 Programming Lead"},"post_url":"/t/swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches/494329/11","custom_user_title":"1294 Programming Lead","reactions":[{"id":"100","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548553,"name":"Benjamin Hall","username":"bhall-ctre","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bhall-ctre/{size}/198180_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T19:42:53.647Z","cooked":"<p>The FieldCentric swerve request defaults to OperatorPerspective, so the template is already correct.</p>
<p>With that said, it is up to the user to correct the robot heading after program startup, as it is initialized to 0 deg regardless of alliance. That means either calling <code>seedFieldCentric()</code> while the robot is facing forward (away from your alliance station wall), or calling <code>resetPose()</code>/<code>resetRotation()</code> with the correct Blue Alliance perspective robot pose/rotation (which is done by PathPlanner/Choreo at the start of auton).</p>","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T19:46:55.073Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":10,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":133,"readers_count":132,"score":76.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":494329,"topic_slug":"swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches","display_username":"Benjamin Hall","primary_group_name":"CTRE","flair_name":"CTRE","flair_url":"/uploads/default/original/3X/1/b/1bd2b430e1bb6427d1c6504ff6abcd31de851a6d.png","flair_bg_color":"","flair_color":"","flair_group_id":57,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":36169,"username":"Hollisms","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":48146,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Software Engineering Intern at CTR Electronics"},"post_url":"/t/swerve-controls-inverted-during-matches/494329/12","custom_user_title":"Software Engineering Intern at CTR Electronics","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":3}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":3,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548618,"name":"Waz","username":"Waz","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/w/7cd45c/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T20:46:09.282Z","cooked":"<p>We have seen similar behavior in our shop and were thinking about possible solutions. The one we saw used last year (“fronts” of robots often faced your alliance wall last year too) and are going to test this evening, is to place the robot facing away from our alliance wall, power up, wait a bit, and then turn it around for the start of the match.</p>
<p>One other option I thought of after looking some more at the code generated by Tuner X, was to change the values of these generated constants (Python) by swapping the 0 and 180 values. And then just place the robot facing our alliance wall and leaving it as such.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">	_BLUE_ALLIANCE_PERSPECTIVE_ROTATION = Rotation2d.fromDegrees(0)
    """Blue alliance sees forward as 0 degrees (toward red alliance wall)"""
    _RED_ALLIANCE_PERSPECTIVE_ROTATION = Rotation2d.fromDegrees(180)
    """Red alliance sees forward as 180 degrees (toward blue alliance wall)"""
</code></pre>
<p>These are only used in the generated code in the subsystem periodic to initialize or update during disable the operator perspective via the <code>SwerveDrivetrain.set_operator_perspective_forward(...)</code> method.</p>
