<p>That would result in your robot odometry being incorrect, as 0 deg needs to be away from the blue alliance station wall (towards the red alliance).</p>
<p>If your robot starts facing 180 deg, the correct way to handle this is by calling <code>reset_rotation(self, Rotation2d)</code> with the correct blue alliance perspective rotation. As long as it is called after you get the alliance station data, you can do:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">drivetrain.runOnce(
