<p>Note for those reading this later, it is <code>get_operator_forward_direction</code> rather than <code>get_operator_forward_perspective</code>.</p>
<p>I have one other closely related question. A couple of weeks ago, one of our programmers added a method to the drive train to zero the robot heading. It fixes the field oriented driving issue, if we orient the robot properly on the field and press the button to run this. But, I now suspect is messes up our odometry.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">    def zeroHeading(self):
