<p>If you know that your current heading (CCW+) from the operator perspective is <code>currentPoseRadians</code>, then you were right the first time, you would call <code>self.reset_rotation(currentPoseRadians + self.get_operator_forward_direction())</code>. So if your robot is facing 90 deg to the left from your perspective, then on the red alliance, 90 deg + 180 deg = -90 deg, which is the correct blue-alliance perspective heading (facing down on the Field2d in your dashboard).</p>
